.SH NAME
SDL_HINT_JOYSTICK_HIDAPI_WII \- A variable controlling whether the HIDAPI driver for Nintendo Wii and Wii U controllers should be used\[char46]
.SH HEADER FILE
Defined in SDL3/SDL_hints\[char46]h

.SH SYNOPSIS
.nf
.B #include \(dqSDL3/SDL.h\(dq
.PP
.BI "#define SDL_HINT_JOYSTICK_HIDAPI_WII "SDL_JOYSTICK_HIDAPI_WII"
.fi
.SH DESCRIPTION
The variable can be set to the following values:


\(bu "0": HIDAPI driver is not used\[char46]

\(bu "1": HIDAPI driver is used\[char46]

This driver doesn't work with the dolphinbar, so the default is

.BR SDL_FALSE
 for now\[char46]

This hint should be set before enumerating controllers\[char46]

